my:Mitigation.my:description: Encrypt the local storage on the device by using a diversified key from a random generated on the device.
Use hardware-backed encryption available on the device.

my:mitigationDecision.my:decisionDetail: Usage of secure enclave on iOS and hardware backed keystore on Android.

my:Risk.my:riskManagmentDetail: Risk reduced through implementation of hardware backed storage.

my:Vulnerability.my:vulnerabilityName: Man in the middle attack through network interception

my:vulnerabilityDescription.div: In all cases, TLS is required for all mobile deployments today on the official stores. The two use-cases possible are :

li.div: Installing a custom CA using social engineering or malware

my:vulnerabilityDescription.div: We are taking the highest CVSS3 scoring between the two use cases above.

my:Vulnerability.my:vulnerabilityName: Dumping of the local storage from a rooted device

my:vulnerabilityDescription.div: When a device is rooted it is possible to completely dump data anywhere on the devices, bypassing the platform's sandbox mechanisms.
Attacker peeks at the user's screen to discover the assets.

ul.li: User interaction required by using the application and accessing / showing confidential data

my:vulnerabilityDescription.div: Attacker logs all the key inputs done by the user, for example a fake keyboard application.

my:Vulnerability.my:vulnerabilityName: Phone backup data analysis of a non-encrypted backup

my:vulnerabilityDescription.div: Attacker makes a backup of the data on the devices or has access to this data and attacks the data backup blob.
